Converting raw data into useful and meaningful statistics which can clearly show the trends in a business to plot the strategy. In Big Data I analyze the variety & veracity of Data to find out the value and vagueness present in the current strategy of a business.

2.	Sentiment Analysis
Analyzing in depth data and making deep neural network models on the tone and style of language. In this domain I analyze the vocabulary to produce the Big Data on a certain perspective which is then branched on the basis of variability yielding sentiment on a scale of negative to positive.

3.	Machine Learning 
I analyze the requirements of our client in depth and the data present with the client. Data is further tokenized based on its root language and features are extracted from it. These features are funneled into a Machine Learning Model using Deep Neural Network or  Decision Trees which can be used for the inference against any test data easily. 

4.	Prediction
In Prediction; First step Machine Learning model is generated and then on the basis of the data a sample dataset is simulated using Time Series simulation or Features Simulation (Approach of Creating Big Data sets using combinations). Simulated data is then tested against the machine learning models to get the prediction of upcoming events.

Name: Tushar G.
Role: CTO turned UX Architect  - in SaaS, RPA, NoCode, Chatbots, Crawling
Description:
I've been a CTO (for past 21yrs), now playing as Product Manager/Designer (for 3yrs).

My clients have often consulted me to "design radical user interface" in their products. These radical UIs often involve forgetting what is possible with conventional engineering and "pushing the state of art" in engineering. I leverage CTO + Product Design skills to show engineers on how they can build some unconventional UIs.

These designs often prompt engineering teams to "code several UI components from scratch". I also help Engineers save their time from "reinventing wheels". This proves beneficial for Product Design teams - because now they can stay creative (yet practical to meet engineering budgets) and offer a unique user experience.

I work with my team of 2 Product Owners, 3 UX Designers, 2 UI Designer, 2 Fine Artists. Our clients are often startups who are building ambitious engineering-heavy products. The products we built for our clients are currently in use at notable places like  US Airforce, Finland Government, Uber, Snapchat, Melinda & Bill Gates Foundation, Ford, and 1000s of Small Medium businesses

The products we designed for our clients, they raised capital from..
.. Notable investors. Like Google Ventures, the European Commission of R&D Office. 
.. Their own bootstrapped money. Later they went on to raise funds successfully from Venture Capitalists, Crowdfunds, and ICOs. 
.. Their customers. Who were paying them for the SaaS products they used.
